<subSubSection pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
Perennial herb, densely hirsute with brownish hairs in all vegetative parts; rootstock woody; stems to c. 1 m, apparently trailing (rarely climbing), relatively stout. Leaves petiolate, 1-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-4 cm, ovate-deltoid, simple, apex acute, margin undulate to irregularly dentate, base cordate; petioles 5-10 (-15) mm. Flowers 1-5; peduncles 2-6.5 cm; pedicels 3-6 (-15) mm; bracteoles 6-12 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, linear, narrowly lanceolate or narrowly oblanceolate; outer sepals 14-18 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7-9 mm, broadly to narrowly ovate, obtuse or acute, margin undulate or crenate; corolla 15-30 mm, white or cream, shallowly lobed, the lobes broadly triangular, acute, c. 5 mm long, the midpetaline bands densely pilose; ovary glabrous, acuminate; style glabrous, divided 5-8 mm above base, stigmas 6 mm, linear. Capsule glabrous; seeds tuberculate. [
<bibRefCitation author="Meeuse, ADL" journalOrPublisher="Bothalia" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="641 - 792" refId="B225" refString="Meeuse, ADL, 1958 1957. The South African Convolvulaceae. Bothalia 6: 641 - 792" title="The South African Convolvulaceae." volume="6" year="1958">Meeuse 1957</bibRefCitation>
: 687; 
<bibRefCitation author="Meeuse, ADL" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Southern Africa" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 138" refId="B226" refString="Meeuse, ADL, Welman, WG, 2000. Convolvulaceae. Flora of Southern Africa volume 28 (part 1): 1 - 138" title="Convolvulaceae." volume="volume 28" year="2000">Meeuse and Welman 2000</bibRefCitation>
: 44 (map)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
South Africa: centred on KwaZula-Natal extending to Eastern Cape, Free State, Lesotho, Swaziland and Northern Province (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Hilliard</emphasis>
5023, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Sanderson</emphasis>
282, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Codd</emphasis>
7655, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Wood</emphasis>
3462, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Rudatis</emphasis>
633, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Strey</emphasis>
3460).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
Distinguished by its tomentose, entire, ovate to oblong, cordate hirsute leaves. Plants described as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. var. var. integrifolia" order="Solanales" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="natalensis" subSpecies="var." variety="integrifolia">var. integrifolia</taxonomicName>
are somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. H. Wright, Fl. Cap. (Harvey) 4 (2): 75. 1904. (Baker and Wright" authorityYear="1904" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus galpinii" order="Solanales" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galpinii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Convolvulus galpinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in leaf shape but 2-3 flowers are borne on each peduncle and the corolla is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernh. ex Krauss, Flora 27 (2): 829. 1844. (Krauss" authorityYear="1844" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus natalensis" order="Solanales" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Convolvulus natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in size.
</paragraph>
